OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FRemaining
OL,6,Fdry, warm but breezy overnight with
OL,7,Fplenty of clear skies. Some patchy
OL,8,Fmist and low cloud however may develop
OL,9,Flater in the night across the east.
OL,10,
OL,11,CMonday:FAny overnight mist and low
OL,12,Fcloud quickly clearing to leave a dry
OL,13,Fand sunny but breezy day across Wales.
OL,14,FFeeling very warm once again as the
OL,15,Fheatwave continues.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
